cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with super resolution, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on using deep learning techniques to estimate the unknown downscaling kernel. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new GAN-based approach for kernel estimation, which falls under the category of generative models and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning techniques and could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing and could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for optimization and could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
